  "notes": "Minangkabau, written today in the Latin script following the Indonesian spelling convention (the Jawi/Arabic tradition is not modelled here). Digraphs: ng /ŋ/, ny /ɲ/, sy /ʃ/, kh /x/. Final ⟨k⟩ is realised as a glottal stop [ʔ]. Five monophthongs /i e a o u/ plus diphthongs (ia, ua, ui, ai, au).",
